claim: Flublok contains 45 micrograms (mcg) of HA per strain vs 15 mcg of HA per strain in a standard-dose influenza vaccine.
explanation: A table of influenza vaccines showing trade names, presentations, age indications, HA content per dose, route, and mercury content. It lists Fluad Quadrivalent (an IIV4) with 15 µg HA per 0.5 mL and Flublok Quadrivalent (a recombinant HA vaccine, RIV4) with 45 µg HA per 0.5 mL. Evidence: Table shows Flublok Quadrivalent contains 45 µg HA per 0.5 mL, whereas Fluad Quadrivalent (IIV4) contains 15 µg HA per 0.5 mL. supports the claim because the table provides data showing Flublok contains 45 µg HA per strain while standard-dose IIV4 vaccines contain 15 µg HA per strain.
